name: Brooklyn Public Library
directions: There's one single stall, non-gendered bathroom at the front of the library. There are going to be renovations, so that might change, but as of February 24th, 2017, this is the case.
comment: You don't have to have a library card or even be using the library.

name: Mission Chinese Food
directions: Accesible bathroom on ground floor, smaller single/ungendered bathrooms downstsairs in the basement
comment: Paying customers

name: ABC beer company
directions: In the back past the bar

name: Subject LES
directions: Main Floor Bar
comment: Owners and Management go to great lengths to make this an inclusive open space.

name: Remedy Diner
directions: To the right around the bar, three bathrooms at back near kitchen
comment: For customers at the diner

name: Cake Shop
directions: On the first floor there's a gender neutral single stall bathroom that's handicapped accessible. There are 2 other bathrooms downstairs that I didn't get a good look at but I believe are also single stall.
comment: They are very laid back and most of the shows there are free so I'd imagine as long as you're quick about it they wouldn't give you a hard time about using the upstairs restroom, or either of the downstairs ones as long as the doors are open. The upstairs one is just past the bar near the door to the basement.

name: Upright Citizens Brigade Theater, East Village
directions: Two single-stall bathrooms in the lobby. ~Four~ single-stall bathrooms in the basement.
comment: Very progressive, cool comedy theater in the East Village. No judgement, guaranteed safe space

name: Two Boots Pizza
directions: By the door in the back.
comment: You have to be a "paying customer" but you can either just buy a soda, or pretend you are waiting in line to buy something and ask the employees to unlock the door for you. It's right by an open door so you can slip out after without buying anything.

name: Associated super market
directions: When you walk in, its to the left all the way in the back corner

name: One & One
directions: Accessible upstairs next to the bar. More inaccessible stalls downstairs
comment: Must be paying customer

name: Starbucks
directions: Follow counter, hang a left, code is on the door. One stall only.

name: Fools Gold NYC
directions: Gender neutral bathroom is located towards the rear of the bar and has historically been adorned with "Everybody Poops" artwork.  The bar has noted that the door was recently replaced due to a broken lock, but that they will be having it repainted shortly.
comment: The bar has confirmed that they are "a trans-friendly location and totally safe bathroom for anyone, especially with the trans/gender non-conforming community."

name: Loreley Beer Garden
directions: first floor, about 1/3 of the way down, on the right-hand side. two gender neutral stalls facing each other. great selfie lighting.
comment: not sure, but likely have to be a paying customer (they have great pretzels, if you need to be a customer to use the bathroom)

name: Bareburger
directions: Straight to the back from the door
comment: Bathroom on the left is accessible.  Both are unisex

name: Au Bon Pain
directions: bathroom is at the back of the shop. enter the door code 0256 then turn the handle to enter

name: Au Bon Pain
directions: by the back of the shop. use the bathroom door code 0256 then turn the handle to get inside

name: Bread Nolita Restaurant
directions: In basement. Stairs or elevator can be taken to use restrooms
comment: Restroom is for paying customers, exceptions sometimes made depending on circumstances.

name: Starbucks
directions: Walk in towards the right and walk straight, keep to the right past the counter, and walk until you hit a wall. Turn left, and you’ll see the bathrooms on the other side of the seating tables. There are two, both gender neutral and single-person.
comment: There is no door code for the bathroom but you can order something and go while they’re making your drink.

name: Seamore's
directions: One upstairs (accessible) one downstairs (not accessible)

name: Target
directions: Bottom floor in a corner

name: Gibney Dance Studios
directions: First floor The the left behind the security desk.
comment: To further enter the building to be able to use the bathroom you have to sign in at the security desk. Best to be a student or customer

name: The Bean
comment: You have to be a paying customer and ask for a key. A small black coffee is $2.50; a small water bottle is $1.50—there might be cheaper stuff available, but I'm not sure.

name: The Bean
comment: You have to be a paying customer and ask for a key. A small black coffee is $2.50; a small water bottle is $1.50—there might be cheaper stuff available, but I'm not sure.

name: Sea Isle City, NJ
directions: On boardwalk just off the beach

name: Pret a manager
directions: At the very back behind cash counter
comment: Ask for code at the registry

name: Starbucks
comment: It's Starbucks you could probably just sneek in

name: Peels Restaurant
directions: On the ground floor, there\\'s a slight step to get into the building, but is easily manageable (I\\'m told) by wheelchair users.
comment: Restaurant is open 7:30am to about 11pm.  If you ask nicely, they'll let you use it with out buying something, but it\\'s appreciated if you buy a cookie or a coffee.  A bit crowded on Brunches.

name: Cucina Liberta
comment: Tourist spot with a lot of foot traffic so they don't check if you're a customer. Handicap accessible via the front. You have to go thru the lobby of the main building and enter via the side lobby entrance.

name: world trade center mall
comment: "family" bathroom, has two toilets inside, use the one closer to the wall so you can reach the tp

name: Finback Brewery
directions: Accessible restroom is in a room to the left when walking in. Other restrooms are to the left of the bar then a left down a short walkway. All are gender neutral.
comment: This is a brewery that has a tasting room with any tables and board games in a wide open space. Great place to meet up with friends and have a good time tasting beer brewed on premise or just talking/playing games. To use the bathroom, you could probably just walk in and head for it - they're also fairly friendly, you could probably just ask or buy a $3 taste.

name: Oculus Beer Garden
directions: Within fenced area, may need to show ID.
comment: Seasonal beer garden.

name: Ninth Ward
directions: Towards the back near the kitchen.
comment: Has three gender-neutral single stall restrooms labelled \"Sex,\" \"Drugs,\" and \"Rock & Roll.\"

name: Nike Soho
directions: Second floor in back.  Elevator accessible.
comment:
(2) Clean, private, unisex rooms.  Completely discreet.  Don’t need to ask for a key.  
Has wifi.

name: 130 Liberty St, New York, NY 10006, USA
directions: 1 on just about every floor, elevators for access
comment: Must buy a ticket to get in because it's the WTC memorial building!

name: NYU
directions: 1 st-6 th Floors- single occupancy unisex, each labeled as ÒRestroomÓ
comment: nyu id required for building access

name: Club Quarters Hotel, World Trade Center
directions: Up the elevator to the 2nd floor, right out of the elevator to the left.
comment: Supposed to be for hotel guests, but if you walk through the lobby and into the elevator like you are staying there nobody will question you.

name: 53 Park Pl, New York, NY 10007, USA
directions: Walk towards back of market. If you stay near fridge items, there should be a white door on the left in between aisles.

name: McDonald's
comment: marked as "family restroom"

name: Leslie-Lohman Museum of Gay and Lesbian Art
directions: Admission: suggested donation $9 (as of sept '18). Restroom is in back right of left side gallery from where you enter. Unfortunately can't remember if there's a changing table.
comment: This is an amazing museum! Saw a beautiful photography exhibit of LGBT daily life 1970s-2000s by photographer Donna Gottschalk.

name: The Public Theater
directions: Through the lobby to the left.

name: The Public Theater
directions: Walk to the back left of the lobby, past the information desk.
comment: Bathrooms are gendered but with the explicit signage that anyone can use the restroom of their choice. During show hours, a gender neutral bathroom can be requested of the house staff. Lobby bathrooms are open to the general public all day.

name: The Drawing Center
directions: two unisex single-stall bathrooms. downstairs behind the reception desk, there are stairs and an elevator.
comment: admission into the further-back main part of the gallery is $5, but I believe you could browse their book area (in the reception lobby) for a bit or just come in and ask about information/hours etc, and then ask to use the bathroom, and they wouldn't give you any grief about not paying.

name: Ihop
directions: In the back
comment: You have to be a paying customer

name: Starbucks
directions: Astor Pl 6 Line stop.
comment: Two restrooms, both gender neutral. Slightly grody due to it being heavily used at time of day visited (weekend night).

name: NYU Bookstore
directions: At the back of the in-store ThinkCoffee which is on the left of the store.
comment: You don't need to be a paying customer or have an NYU id to gain access

name: Korchma Taras Bulba
street: 357 West Broadway, New York, NY 10013, USA
directions: In the back.
comment: Sit-down restaurant with bar. Drinks are $10-14.

name: NYU - Gallatin Building
directions: 4th, 5th, 6th Floor- single occupancy unisex, labeled as 'Restroom'
comment: nyu id required for access

name: Webster Hall
directions: Basement of venue

name: NYU Tisch School of the Arts
directions: They're on the 9th, 10th, and 11th floors. Tisch building is also a safe space to use the gendered bathroom that you assign with.
comment: You must be an NYU student.

name: Warren Weaver Hall
directions: first floor, south end.
comment: Two single-occupancy genderfree bathrooms, one accessible.You need to show NYU ID, but you can probably just flash any purple card with a picture as you walk by, the guards never look very closely.  You may be able to just ask nicely as well.Sometimes the emergency exit on the west side towards the south is open, in which case you can enter there without ID.

name: NYU Tisch Schhol of the Arts
directions: 9th floor, straight down the hall, on your left almost at the end of the hall there are 2 single stall, fairly accessible restrooms
comment: You have to have an NYU ID or be a guest of an NYU student to get past the guard. Sometimes they won't ask for ID if you walk in like you own the place, but that depends entirely on the guard on duty at the time.

name: Lombardi’s
directions: In the back of the restaurant, there is a sign pointing towards the restroom

name: Dunkin Donuts
comment: Need to be buzzed into the bathroom by the cashier

name: Dunkin Donuts
comment: Need to be buzzed into the bathroom by the cashier

name: Bubby’s
directions: Downstairs

name: Peridance-Capezio Center
directions: One on ground floor, one on second floor. Ground floor bathroom is to left of entrance by staircase.

name: NYU
directions: 7th Floor- single occupancy unisex, labeled as ÒRestroomÓ 10th Floor- single occupancy unisex, labeled as ÒRestroomÓ 3rd Floor- single occupancy unisex, labeled as ÒRestroomÓ 1st Floor- single occupancy unisex, labeled as ÒRestroomÓ
comment: NYU id required for entry to building

name: Falchi Building
directions: First floor lobby, down the hallway across from the security desk
comment: Public, no purchases required

name: NYU Stern School of Business
directions: On each floor of the Kaufman Management Center at Stern

name: NYU Stern School of Business
directions: On each floor of the Kaufman Management Center at Stern

name: The Phluid Project
directions: All the way back and next to the coffee bar :)

name: The Phluid Project
directions: Walk in and go all the way to the back and it’s right next to the coffee bar :)

name: New York University Department of English
directions: There is one single stall, gender neutral room on the first floor and another on the third floor.
comment: These are only accessible to NYU students.

name: Bareburger
directions: Straight back to the right.
comment: Should be a paying customer. Depends how the host is feeling

name: Think Coffee
directions: Two-thirds of the way back, just past the barista station, on the right.
comment: I haven't ever tried to use the restroom here without buying something, so I don't know how much of a fuss they'd kick up about it if you didn't.

name: Bareburger
directions: all the way in the back by the bar
comment: must be a customer

name: Bareburger
directions: Back right past the bar
comment: Probably have to be a customer

name: NYU - Schwartz Building
directions: 11th floor
comment: nyu id required to enter building

name: The YinOva Center
directions: Ask the Front Desk as you enter, they will show you where to go.
comment: We are an acupuncture clinic primarily and our bathrooms are for our patients. However, if you come in quietly and ask our front desk if you can use the restroom, they will happily show you the way. We just ask for quiet voices and respect of our clinic in return.

name: Adelphi Manhattan Center School of Social Work
directions: When you enter the campus, the bathrooms are the first left right next to the entrance doors. The gender-neutral bathroom is along the wall, so you'll need to turn around at the end of the hallway to see it.
comment: You'll need to show ID on the first floor to get a visitor's pass to enter the building, and you'll need to sign in at the Adelphi front desk. If you're an Adelphi student, you can use your student ID for both checkpoints. The Adelphi campus is a safe space, so no worries about harassment.

name: Strand Bookstore
directions: 2nd floor, back of the kids section, there are trad. gendered bathrooms to the left of the desk but a single-stall/genderfree bathroom to the right of the desk.

name: Silver School of Social Work, New York University
directions: 2-3 bathrooms gender-neutral on each floor (basement-4th floor). Elevators are on the right side of the hallway once you enter the building to the right of the staircase. Continue past the elevator to the end of the hallway and restrooms are on the right.
comment: Must be an NYU student or faculty with ID to enter unless there is an event open to the public; there are stairs to enter into the main entrance of the NYU Silver School of Social Work building.

name: NYU - Kimmel Center for University Life
directions: 1 st Floor-single occupancy unisex, labeled as ÒRestroomÓ
comment: NYU ID card required to enter building

name: Yasashi Tokushu Sei
directions: This Restroom is inside of the Mount Sinai Beth Israel Emergency Room, of which is only required to ask upon entry to utilise the Restroom.
comment: The Restroom is often kept extremely clean when compared with most public Restrooms in Manhattan (also known as New York New York). I do not suggest utilising the Emergency Room Psychiatric Impatient Unit Facility, because the Employees are Savage also violent.

name: ABC Kitchen
street: East 18th Street, New York, NY, USA
directions: Left side by the front entrance

name: Bard High School Early College Queens
directions: 6th Floor, down hallway to left, past double doors
comment: Is located in a school and you likely won't be let in without some sort of student ID or guest pass - speak with the security officers at the desk.

name: by CHLOE.
directions: Near the counter where you order or pick up your food

name: By Chloe
comment: Just act like you're looking at the menu

name: The Grey Dog
comment: *should* be a paying customer, but they're often busy enough/get enough traffic that walking with a purpose should be fine.

name: Spice
directions: It is all the way in the back on the ground floor
comment: This is a restaurant, so you may have to actually be eating there to use it. Or try asking the person at the front desk.

name: Parsons Fine Arts
directions: Fifth floor on the south/west side of the building.
comment: Enter with New School ID. Good place to poop. Also has a sharps container!

name: Dog & Bone
directions: At the back of the pib
comment: Two gender neutral, single person washrooms

name: Bravo Pizza
directions: In the back and to the left
comment: It says it's for customers only, but the place is big and usually crowded so no one will notice you if you just walk over there

name: Union Square
directions: 13th floor at the end of the hallway, passcode is 3140
comment: Passcode: 3140

name: Baruch College- Vertical Campus
directions: Next to the cafe in the book store
comment: You don’t have to sign into the building or buy anything, just act casual, they’ve never said anything to me. Knock first.

name: Legal Action Center
comment: You have to be on the security list to get into the building. But if you have an appointment with any of the businesses in the building (at least on the fourth floor but probably other floors too) you'll be able to use a single stall bathroom.

name: Starbucks
directions: Two ungendered single bathrooms

name: Lowery
directions: Individual unisex stalls with handwash station outside restrooms

name: Bosie Tea Parlor
directions: In the back of the restaurant
comment: just ask :) everyone's friendly and a good portion of the staff are queer

name: Rafele - Italian Restaurant
directions: left of the bar with handicap symbol

name: Umami Burger
directions: To the right of the door to the kitchen.
comment: Two gender-neutral locking single-stalls. The first room has accessibility handrails.
